   Pro football Hall of Famer Roger Staubach has
made an appeal to President Bush to help out some of his pilot
friends at Eastern Airlines, which has been on strike for five
months and is in Chapter 11 bankruptcy.
   The former Dallas Cowboys quarterback asked in a letter dated
Aug. 1 that a meeting be set up between representatives of the
Eastern pilots union and Roger Porter, Bush's domestic policy
adviser.
