<FIRST>u i AM-Obit-DominicBehan     08-04 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Dominic Behan,0149</SECOND>
<HEAD>Dominic Behan, Playwright and Brother of Brendan Behan, Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLASGOW, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dominic Behan, a playwright and
balladeer whose brother was the late writer Brendan Behan, has died
at age 61, his family said Friday.
   He died Thursday after an illness of several months, the family
said.
   Dominic Behan's first novel, ``The Public World of Parable
Jones,'' was published this year.
   Among his plays was ``Posterity for the Damned,'' a reflection
on what he viewed as the follies of the Irish Republican Army,
staged at the Gaiety Theater in Dublin in 1959.
   His play ``The Folk Singer,'' a series of songs about Northern
Ireland, appeared on Northern Ireland television in 1972. Among his
other songs were ``The Patriot Game'' and ``Liverpool Lou.''
   Dominic Behan is survived by his wife, Josephine, and sons
Fintan and Stephen.
   Brendan Behan died in 1964.
</TEXT>
