<HEAD>London Stock Index Posts 1989 High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices surged Friday in heavy trading with
the key British index closing at a new high for this year.
   Strong investor interest in insurance and pharmaceutical stocks,
combined with news of a sweetened $1.5 billion offer by Boots Co.
PLC for Ward White Group PLC, underscored the market's rise.
   Dealers said investors interpreted the renewal of speculative
interest as an excuse to push prices higher, thus giving a
technical twist to the market's rise.
   ``There's no real selling pressure at all because people are
afraid of being left out when the market makes its next move
forward,'' one dealer said.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed up
21.2 points, or 0.9 percent, at 2,327.5.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended up 16.8 points at
1,940.8. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 10.21 points to
close at 1,312.74.
   Volume totaled a robust 731.4 million shares Friday, compared
with 550.1 million shares Thursday.
