<FIRST>r f BC-OilDiscovery     08-04 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Oil Discovery,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Arco Confirms Large Oil Discovery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Test wells have confirmed the discovery
of a major oil reservoir near the Prudhoe Bay field on Alaska's
North Slope, Arco Alaska Inc. said Friday.
   Arco Alaska, a division of Atlantic Richfield Co., said a test
well 2{ miles west of the 1988 discovery well at Point McIntyre
produced flow rates up to 5,400 barrels a day. Arco spokeswoman
Susan Andrews said that would make it one of the largest oil
discoveries in the United States in the last 10 years.
   Arco estimates the reservoir, two miles north of the Prudhoe Bay
field, contains 300 million barrels. Prudhoe Bay, the nation's
largest oilfield, contained an estimated 10 billion barrels.
   ``With testing completed on these two delineation wells, we have
confirmed the presence of a high-quality reservoir with good
porosity and permeability,'' said Jerry Dees, vice president of
exploration for Arco.
   Exxon Corp. and BP Exploration, a unit of British Petroleum Co.
PLC, are Arco's partners in the Point McIntyre field.
</TEXT>
