<HEAD>Stock Price Falls After Big Jump</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Walt Disney Co.'s stock price fell nearly $5
per share Friday after rising $11.25 the previous two days as
speculation that it was a takeover target died down.
   Disney shares dropped $4.87{ a share to close at $116.12{ in
active trading on the New York Stock Exchange.
   Harold Vogel, entertainment analyst with Merrill Lynch Research
in New York, attributed the decline to reports dismissing a
takeover of Disney as unlikely, including a column by Dan Dorfman
in USA Today.
